main event: Civilian witnesses observed multiple oval-shaped, pinkish-white objects with a high-pitched hum over Tempe, Arizona on September 8, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were arranged in a formation, with four objects together and two others following behind.
The objects had small, shiny windows emitting a Finnish-like light.
The high-pitched hum from the objects gave the main witness a headache and his wife a shock.
The objects performed a rapid climb and appeared to be descending to land before disappearing beyond the Superstition Mountains.
The main witness has reported seeing numerous similar objects in the area, typically between 11:30 PM and 3:00 AM near the Superstition Mountains.
